## Content rules

- Cite `RULE-<PREFIX>-<NN>` IDs when auditing. Fabricated rules are the largest source of false positives — if a rule is not in the loaded `rules/` file, do not invent one.
- Prefer stating uncertainty over guessing. If the user asks about a feature or method not covered in the loaded sources, say so and link the upstream doc rather than extrapolating.
- Explain the *why* behind recommendations. YDB has non-obvious invariants (partition locality, server-side serializability, query-cache plan reuse keyed on the parameterized query text) that drive the right answer; naming the invariant makes the guidance transferable to the next case the user will hit.
